title: India calls Pakistan's claim of targeted killings 'false'
content: Islamabad on Thursday accused India of killing two of its citizens on its soil in riot 2023.

title: Tamil Nadu: Chennai’s 'last Jew' fights for place in India’s history
content: Davvid Levi has been documenting the history of his family and that of other Jews in India's Chennai city.

title: India v England: 'Hyderabad Heist shows England are unmissable'
content: The astonishing victory over India in Hyderabad shows why you cannot take your eyes off the England Test team, says Stephan Shemilt.

title: Rohan Bopanna: 'Age is just a number'
content: India's Rohan Bopanna, 43, becomes the oldest men's doubles Grand Slam champion with victory at the Australian Open.

title: Adani Ports: The Tamil Nadu villagers taking on a billionaire's port plan
content: Locals in 100 villages of Tamil Nadu state are fighting the expansion of a port owned by Gautam Adani.

title: Umar Khalid: Indian activist languishes in jail without bail or trial
content: Umar Khalid, who was arrested three years ago for alleged involvement in riots, is still waiting for a trial.

title: Women take the lead in Republic Day parade
content: Every year, the country celebrates the day its constitution came into effect with a grand spectacle.

title: Watch: Crowds at India's new Ram temple in Ayodhya day after opening
content: The grand temple dedicated to the Hindu God Ram was inaugurated by Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Monday.

title: Indian PM Modi inaugurates temple in Ayodhya
content: The opening of the grand temple comes ahead of India's general elections.

title: Plane gets jammed under bridge in India
content: The scrap fuselage was on its way to Assam from Mumbai on a lorry when it got stuck.

title: Intruder jumps on table in Indian parliament
content: Lawmakers said two men jumped into the well of the house from the visitors' gallery.

title: Moment worker is pulled from collapsed tunnel
content: Fourty-one Indian workers are finally rescued from a tunnel that partially caved in after a landslide.

title: First video of trapped tunnel workers in India
content: Rescuers have shared a video of the 41 workers who have been trapped inside a tunnel since 12 November.
